description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assistant Practitioner Band 4 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Team - Melksham and Bradford on Avon &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours/ Week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently require a Band 4 Assistant Practitioner to work in the Melksham and Bradford-on-Avon Community Team. You will have a small delegated caseload to work with and will support the trained staff with therapeutic/clinical interventions and administrative tasks. Your main role will be to support the therapy team with Home First and you will undertake Home First reviews. You will be expected to work in patients’ homes, in community clinical settings and to link closely with the GP Practices in the Melksham and Bradford-on-Avon areas as well as the local acute hospitals. You will be based within the team at Melksham Hospital. The hour of work will be 08.30 to 16.30hrs and you may occasionally be asked to work a weekend or a late shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in front line NHS community patient care is essential as is evidence of up to date clinical-based skills development. Applicants need to have well developed communication skills, a good IT knowledge, evidence of basic therapy skills and will need to be able to work under pressure. The role is demanding but rewarding, and we are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and hardworking individuals who can work flexibly and efficiently&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy, friendly team, who would welcome the opportunity to work with a new member of staff willing to contribute to the ongoing development of the services we provide.&lt;/p&gt;
